Detect Color¶


  • Show image, with nearest neighbour interpolation plt.imshow(image, interpolation='nearest')

  • Blur image cv2.GaussianBlur(image, (7, 7), 0)

  • Detect Color cv2.inRange(image_blur_hsv, min_red, max_red)
  • Cleaning, used morphology technique to close (fill voids / blanks space) and then open (remove small specks).
    kernel = cv2.getStructuringElement(cv2.MORPH_ELLIPSE, (15, 15))
    • Filling small gaps image_red_closed = cv2.morphologyEx(image_red, cv2.MORPH_CLOSE, kernel)
    • Removing small specs specks image_red_closed_then_opened = cv2.morphologyEx(image_red_closed, cv2.MORPH_OPEN, kernel)

Extracting text from Image (OCR)¶



  • Python-tesseract is used for optical character recognition (OCR) tool for python. To download binary: https://github.com/UB-Mannheim/tesseract/wiki
  • setting threshold retval, threshold = cv2.threshold(image,127,255,cv2.THRESH_BINARY)
    • different thrheshold techniques: https://docs.opencv.org/3.4.0/d7/d4d/tutorial_py_thresholding.html
  • run tesseract, which gives us string as an output. text = pytesseract.image_to_string(threshold)

Detect Contours in Images¶

  • Convert the image to a binary thresholded image _, binary = cv2.threshold(gray, 225, 255, cv2.THRESH_BINARY_INV)

  • find the contours from the thresholded image contours, hierarchy = cv2.findContours(binary, cv2.RETR_TREE, cv2.CHAIN_APPROX_SIMPLE)

  • draw all contours image = cv2.drawContours(image, contours, -1, (0, 255, 0), 2)
